# Changelog

All notable changes to this project are documented in this file.

The format is based on [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.1.0/),
and this project adheres to [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0.html).

## [Unreleased]

### Added

- Project documentation set under `docs/`, plus this changelog and a contributing guide.
- Dependency-injected sink registration: `ISinkRegistration`, `DiSinkFactory`, `DefaultSinks`, and the
  `AddDataGenTargets` and `AddSink` service-collection extensions. See
  [ADR-0007](docs/architecture/decisions/adr-0007-di-sink-registration.md).
- All remaining storage targets implemented as concrete sinks: Azure Blob Storage, Azure Files, Azure Data
  Share, OneLake Lakehouse, Azure SQL Database, OneLake Warehouse, PostgreSQL, Azure Cosmos DB, Azure AI Search,
  Azure Service Bus, Azure Event Grid, Fabric Eventhouse, Dataverse, and Databricks Unity Catalog.
- A configuration sample per target under `samples/targets/`.
- The Azure Functions host resolves `ISinkFactory` through dependency injection (`AddDataGenTargets`).
- Industries and entity names moved to editable JSON in the configuration (`industries.json`, `entities.json`)
  exposed by `ReferenceCatalog`, with a `DataGen.CatalogExporter` tool to regenerate them from a workbook. The
  configuration editor loads these as validated dropdowns for the Industry, Entity name, and Schema area fields.
- A configuration editor host, `DataGen.ConfigEditor`, a WinForms property-grid editor for the run
  configuration that reads and writes run-config JSON and stores its reference lists and preferences in local
  JSON files (locales, source types, target templates, settings).
- Output localization for generated values: a run-level `locale` (default `en-US`) with a per-entity override,
  a `LocaleCatalog` of supported locales and languages stored as embedded configuration resources, validation
  of configured locales, the locale carried into the Foundry prompt, and locale selectors in the WinForms client.

## [0.1.0] - 2026-06-28

The first working version: the Core engine, the configuration layer, Foundry value
generation, six concrete target adapters, four hosts, and Application Insights logging.

### Added

- **Core engine** (`DataGen.Core`): day-part calculator, schedule evaluator, boost-date
  ramp calculator, real-time rate accumulator, batch planner, identity pool, value
  coordinator, and the generation orchestrator.
- **Abstractions** (`DataGen.Abstractions`): the run-configuration and catalog model,
  the `IValueProvider`, `ISink`, and `ISinkFactory` interfaces, and the generated-data types.
- **Configuration** (`DataGen.Configuration`): a streaming workbook catalog reader, the
  run-config JSON loader, and a validator that checks a run against the catalog.
- **Foundry value generation** (`DataGen.Generation.Foundry`): an `IValueProvider` that
  calls an Azure AI Foundry chat deployment with structured outputs and coerces results to
  CDM types.
- **Target adapters** (`DataGen.Targets`): `JsonFileSink`, `ConsoleSink`, `NullSink`,
  `AdlsGen2Sink` (NDJSON), `AdlsGen2ParquetSink` (Parquet), and `EventHubsSink`. The
  remaining workbook storage targets resolve to a scaffolded stub that names the package
  needed to finish each adapter.
- **Hosts**: a PowerShell binary module, an Azure Functions isolated worker, a WinForms
  desktop client, and an Azure AI Foundry agent tool.
- **Logging** (`DataGen.Observability`): `ILogger` across every tier, routed to Azure
  Application Insights, with a delegate provider so a host can mirror logs into its own UI.
- **Tests**: `DataGen.Core.Tests` (42 tests) and `DataGen.Targets.Tests` (17 tests),
  covering the boost math, scheduling, accrual, batch cadence, the value coordinator, the
  NDJSON and Parquet writers, path building, and factory wiring.

### Decisions

- Single `net10.0` target across the solution. See
  [ADR-0001](docs/architecture/decisions/adr-0001-single-net10-target.md).
- Boost windows are symmetric with `daysBefore`. See
  [ADR-0002](docs/architecture/decisions/adr-0002-boost-symmetric-window.md).
- Boost overlap resolves strongest-wins. See
  [ADR-0003](docs/architecture/decisions/adr-0003-boost-overlap-strongest-wins.md).
- Day-part and boost scale batch size, not cadence. See
  [ADR-0004](docs/architecture/decisions/adr-0004-batch-size-scaling.md).
- Foundry produces semantic values; the engine stamps system fields. See
  [ADR-0005](docs/architecture/decisions/adr-0005-foundry-value-generation.md).
- Logging uses `ILogger` with Application Insights at the host boundary. See
  [ADR-0006](docs/architecture/decisions/adr-0006-ilogger-application-insights.md).

